<div class="hero">
  <div class="hero-inner">
    <div class="badge"><span class="badge-dot"></span>Interactive · 3 minutes · 10 questions</div>
    <h1 class="hero-h">AI readiness <em style="color:#00C853;font-style:italic;">scorecard.</em></h1>
    <p class="hero-sub">
      A 10-question assessment that scores your organization on AI readiness across 5 dimensions: leadership, governance, tooling, workflows, and team capability. Get a tier (Laggard, Transitional, Competitive, or Leader) plus specific next steps based on your weakest pillar.
    </p>
  </div>
</div>

<section>
  <div class="sec-inner">
    <div class="quiz">
      <div class="progress" id="progress"></div>

      <div class="q active" data-q="0" data-dim="Leadership">
        <div class="q-dim">Dimension 1 · Leadership</div>
        <h3>How would you describe your CEO's personal AI use?</h3>
        <div class="opts">
          <button class="opt" data-score="4">Uses AI daily on real work, builds Custom GPTs/Claude Projects, has strong intuition for what AI can/can't do</button>
          <button class="opt" data-score="3">Uses AI regularly, has personal workflows, comfortable evaluating AI strategy</button>
          <button class="opt" data-score="2">Has tried AI, uses it occasionally, but not part of daily workflow</button>
          <button class="opt" data-score="1">Knows AI matters but hasn't personally used it meaningfully</button>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="q" data-q="1" data-dim="Leadership">
        <div class="q-dim">Dimension 1 · Leadership</div>
        <h3>Is there a named executive accountable for AI strategy?</h3>
        <div class="opts">
          <button class="opt" data-score="4">Yes — named exec with explicit mandate and budget authority</button>
          <button class="opt" data-score="3">Yes informally — a senior person leads it, but accountability is shared</button>
          <button class="opt" data-score="2">No formal owner, but the CEO or COO informally drives it</button>
          <button class="opt" data-score="1">No one owns it — diffuse "everyone uses AI"</button>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="q" data-q="2" data-dim="Governance">
        <div class="q-dim">Dimension 2 · Governance</div>
        <h3>Do you have a written AI usage policy?</h3>
        <div class="opts">
          <button class="opt" data-score="4">Yes — written, current, includes approved tools / prohibited uses / verification standards / review cadence</button>
          <button class="opt" data-score="3">Yes — but it's basic or older than 6 months</button>
          <button class="opt" data-score="2">We have informal norms but nothing written</button>
          <button class="opt" data-score="1">No policy — anyone uses whatever AI they want</button>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="q" data-q="3" data-dim="Governance">
        <div class="q-dim">Dimension 2 · Governance</div>
        <h3>What's your stance on client confidential data + AI?</h3>
        <div class="opts">
          <button class="opt" data-score="4">Written policy with clear permitted/prohibited categories; team has been trained on it</button>
          <button class="opt" data-score="3">Verbal guidance from leadership; mostly followed but not formalized</button>
          <button class="opt" data-score="2">We've talked about it but no clear stance yet</button>
          <button class="opt" data-score="1">Haven't addressed this — assume people are figuring it out individually</button>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="q" data-q="4" data-dim="Tooling">
        <div class="q-dim">Dimension 3 · Tooling</div>
        <h3>Which AI tools is the team using for serious work?</h3>
        <div class="opts">
          <button class="opt" data-score="4">Team-deployed Claude Team or ChatGPT Team/Enterprise + specialized tools (Perplexity, Gong, etc.)</button>
          <button class="opt" data-score="3">Most people have Claude Pro or ChatGPT Plus individually; no team deployment yet</button>
          <button class="opt" data-score="2">A few power users have AI subscriptions; most don't</button>
          <button class="opt" data-score="1">No formal AI tools deployed; people might be using free tier ChatGPT</button>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="q" data-q="5" data-dim="Tooling">
        <div class="q-dim">Dimension 3 · Tooling</div>
        <h3>Are you using shared Claude Projects (or ChatGPT GPTs) with team-level system prompts?</h3>
        <div class="opts">
          <button class="opt" data-score="4">Yes — multiple shared Projects with ICP, voice, and reference docs loaded</button>
          <button class="opt" data-score="3">A few shared Projects exist but inconsistent adoption</button>
          <button class="opt" data-score="2">Each person has their own personal Projects; nothing shared</button>
          <button class="opt" data-score="1">We don't use Projects/GPTs at all yet</button>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="q" data-q="6" data-dim="Workflows">
        <div class="q-dim">Dimension 4 · Workflows</div>
        <h3>Where does AI currently show up in daily team workflows?</h3>
        <div class="opts">
          <button class="opt" data-score="4">Integrated across 4+ functions (sales, marketing, ops, finance/HR) with measurable output changes</button>
          <button class="opt" data-score="3">Strong adoption in 2-3 functions; spreading to others</button>
          <button class="opt" data-score="2">Used informally for one-off tasks; no integrated workflows</button>
          <button class="opt" data-score="1">Limited to occasional drafting assists by individuals</button>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="q" data-q="7" data-dim="Workflows">
        <div class="q-dim">Dimension 4 · Workflows</div>
        <h3>Can you point to specific measurable outcomes AI has produced in the last 90 days?</h3>
        <div class="opts">
          <button class="opt" data-score="4">Yes — specific metrics: content output up X%, prep time down Y%, customer response time cut by Z hours</button>
          <button class="opt" data-score="3">Anecdotally yes, but we don't have hard numbers</button>
          <button class="opt" data-score="2">Hard to tell — the team likes the tools but output hasn't visibly changed</button>
          <button class="opt" data-score="1">No measurable outcomes yet</button>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="q" data-q="8" data-dim="Team capability">
        <div class="q-dim">Dimension 5 · Team capability</div>
        <h3>Has your team gone through structured AI training (not just a single workshop)?</h3>
        <div class="opts">
          <button class="opt" data-score="4">Yes — multi-session cohort training with role-specific content and ongoing reinforcement</button>
          <button class="opt" data-score="3">Yes — at least one substantial workshop or session, plus internal docs</button>
          <button class="opt" data-score="2">A one-time intro session or Loom video; mostly self-taught from there</button>
          <button class="opt" data-score="1">No formal training — people figured it out themselves</button>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="q" data-q="9" data-dim="Team capability">
        <div class="q-dim">Dimension 5 · Team capability</div>
        <h3>Is AI fluency a hiring criterion now?</h3>
        <div class="opts">
          <button class="opt" data-score="4">Yes — explicit in JDs, tested in interviews, weighted in decisions</button>
          <button class="opt" data-score="3">Mentioned in JDs but not deeply evaluated in interviews</button>
          <button class="opt" data-score="2">A nice-to-have we sometimes consider</button>
          <button class="opt" data-score="1">Not part of our hiring process</button>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="result" id="result">
        <div class="tier" id="tier-name">Competitive</div>
        <div class="tier-score" id="tier-score">Score: 30/40</div>
        <p class="body" id="tier-desc"></p>

        <div class="pillars" id="pillars"></div>

        <div class="next-steps">
          <h4 id="ns-h">What to do next</h4>
          <p id="ns-intro"></p>
          <ul id="ns-list"></ul>
        </div>

        <div style="margin-top:1.5rem;display:flex;gap:1rem;flex-wrap:wrap;">
          <button class="btn-g" onclick="window.location.reload()">Retake</button>
          <a href="/ai-cmo-advisor" class="btn-p">Get the $99 report →</a>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="nav-row" id="navrow">
        <button class="btn-g" id="back" style="visibility:hidden">← Back</button>
        <span id="qcount" style="color:#8FAF8F;font-size:0.85rem;align-self:center;">Question 1 of 10</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section>
  <div class="sec-inner">
    <span class="lbl">Related</span>
    <h2 class="h2">Related resources</h2>
    <ul style="list-style:none;padding:0;color:#C0D8C0;font-size:0.95rem;line-height:1.85;">
